1
00:00:00,417 --> 00:00:08,550
[GEMINI BY JULIE ANNE SAN JOSE PLAYING]

2
00:00:09,217 --> 00:00:12,053
It is called dissociative amnesia.

3
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:15,682
Godfather said he would
mix my drinks with drugs.

4
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:18,101
What happened to you,
what you experienced,

5
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,061
was a trauma response.

6
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:24,983
It’s your brain’s defense mechanism
to erase bad memories.

7
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:26,985
I’m Hector.

8
00:00:27,986 --> 00:00:28,945
Liv’s father.

9
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,572
We've seen each other before.

10
00:00:32,073 --> 00:00:33,700
In Zach’s office.

11
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,494
The day he died.

12
00:00:45,503 --> 00:00:47,255
Are you sure of what you saw?

13
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:49,883
Yes.

14
00:00:50,175 --> 00:00:56,305
After Zach and I talked, I returned to
his office because I couldn’t help it.

15
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,391
He’s the one I saw there.

16
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,935
I was a bit confused.

17
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:05,565
He was holding some eye drops
without removing his glasses.

18
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:06,816
Dad, is that true?

19
00:01:07,358 --> 00:01:09,736
Why? Did I say anything wrong?

20
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:14,074
Zach died because someone
poured eye drops in his drink.

21
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:16,326
It can be fatal when a lot of it is ingested.

22
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:19,537
I thought Zach died because of the fire?

23
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:22,123
That was what we concluded initially.

24
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:28,296
But the investigation showed that
eye drops were used to kill Zach.

25
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:30,423
Why are you looking at me like that?

26
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,634
Because you have lot of explaining to do.

27
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:35,844
You'd better come with
us to the precinct

28
00:01:35,845 --> 00:01:37,013
- so you’ll be able to explain-
- [LIV] No!

29
00:01:38,056 --> 00:01:39,891
Send us a subpoena first,

30
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:42,268
before we come with you to the precinct

31
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:44,729
with our lawyer.

32
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:47,148
[AMELIE VOICEOVER] The only grand finale in
the search for justice

33
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:49,567
is when the real suspect faces the truth.

34
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:54,697
The victims find peace, and no
loose ends are left hanging.

35
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:59,285
[GEMINI BY JULIE ANNE SAN JOSE PLAYING]

36
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:37,615
- [YANA SNIFFLES]
- Yana, can we talk?

37
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:42,370
Please wait.

38
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:45,706
Yana, I know you’re going
through something difficult.

39
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:49,335
But I don’t think it’s bad for me
to ask you to treat me well.

40
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:50,295
Is that so?

41
00:02:50,296 --> 00:02:51,587
I didn’t leave you.

42
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:52,964
I didn’t abandon you.

43
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:55,466
And now you're rubbing it in, huh?

44
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:57,050
Yana, what I’m trying to say is

45
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:59,304
don’t push away the people
who care for you.

46
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:03,600
Liv, Sugar, me.

47
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:06,518
- We love you.
- Nobody loves me now, Gabo.

48
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:07,729
I love you.

49
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:10,398
Even if your heart is rock solid.

50
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:14,402
[YANA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

51
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:16,070
You’re so lame.

52
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,240
That’s why I don’t like you at all.

53
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,576
Can’t you see?

54
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:24,829
I just lost my dad.

55
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:30,376
So, if you will excuse me,
I have a funeral to prepare.

56
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:32,545
[YANA SCOFFS]

57
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,507
[GABO SIGHS]

58
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:40,136
That Inspector Catapang is something else.

59
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:44,015
No wonder he was taken off Zach’s case.

60
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:46,684
Because he is easily fooled by anybody.

61
00:03:46,976 --> 00:03:49,312
He doesn’t even have any solid evidence.

62
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:52,482
But don’t worry, Dad.

63
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,401
Your name will be cleared.

64
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:57,278
They will find the real suspect.

65
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:11,251
Are you okay, Dad?

66
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:13,544
Yeah.

67
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:15,838
Hey, are you okay?

68
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:17,507
What’s wrong?

69
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:19,926
I love you so much, Liv.

70
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:29,852
Mrs. Zamora surrendered her phone.

71
00:04:31,646 --> 00:04:35,775
The video she took the day
Zach died was also authenticated.

72
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,319
She was at the crime scene.

73
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:43,199
Hector Baltazar had the
means to kill the victim.

74
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:48,079
The brand of the eye drops
used to poison Zach is

75
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:50,915
the same brand of the
company where Liv works.

76
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,751
It is possible that Liv
gave a bottle to her dad.

77
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:57,297
And that’s the method used by Mr. Baltazar.

78
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:59,507
But what’s his motive?

79
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:04,679
It’s possible that he didn't like Zach for Liv.

80
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:13,938
He had the means, the method,
and the motive.

81
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:19,068
We found our potential killer!

82
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,368
Hi Dad.

83
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:32,498
I hope you’re happy.

84
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:37,170
Especially now that you are with Mom.

85
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:42,842
I feel super stressed right now.

86
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:45,845
It’s my finals week in law school.

87
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:47,889
I’m studying really hard.

88
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:50,641
I don’t want to fail.

89
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:01,361
I just want to say goodbye to your dad.

90
00:06:04,238 --> 00:06:05,782
And to you as well.

91
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,037
Why?

92
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:14,791
Are you leaving?

93
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,461
I got accepted for that job in
the cruise ship that I applied for.

94
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:20,046
The offer is good.

95
00:06:20,546 --> 00:06:23,716
And the training will start two weeks from now.

96
00:06:25,968 --> 00:06:27,220
That was quick.

97
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,181
If you want me to stay, I will be okay with that.

98
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:31,432
Why?

99
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:33,851
You already applied for the job, right?

100
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,771
Then, go. Leave.

101
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,649
So it is fine with you if I’m just gone?

102
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:42,527
Why wouldn’t it be fine with me?

103
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,904
It’s not like I need you anyway, okay?

104
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:46,113
I’m used to being alone.

105
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,824
Yana.

106
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:54,038
I’m hoping that maybe you want me to stay.

107
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:56,874
That you want to be with me.

108
00:06:58,084 --> 00:07:02,088
I am also hoping that
maybe you love me, too.

109
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:05,174
Because I already told you, Yana,

110
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:06,843
that I love you.

111
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:08,678
So what?

112
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:11,681
I know that you like me, too.

113
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:14,225
That’s bold of you to say.

114
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:16,477
Come on, just tell me the truth.

115
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:19,439
Just tell me once, and I will not leave.

116
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:20,481
I will stay with you.

117
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,818
I don’t need you, okay?

118
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:28,071
Besides, I’m already used to being alone.

119
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:31,284
So, if you will excuse me,
I have an exam to study for.

120
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:33,703
Yana.

121
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:37,582
Playing hard to get!

122
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,149
Forgive me, Liv.

123
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:32,887
[KNOCKING ON WOOD]

124
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,472
Anybody home?

125
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,182
[KNOCKING ON WOOD]

126
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:39,477
[DOOR OPENS]

127
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:42,939
Inspector,

128
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:44,815
do you know what time it is?

129
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:45,816
Have you checked?

130
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:46,984
It's still early

131
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,320
and you're already
causing a disturbance here.

132
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:52,573
Is Mr. Hector Baltazar here?

133
00:08:52,907 --> 00:08:54,450
And what do you want from him?

134
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:56,786
Go look for him inside!

135
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,913
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, hey, wait!
- [LEONA] Hey!

136
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:01,165
[STAMMERS] Hey what's going on?
This is clearly a violation, right?

137
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:03,792
We can sue you for harassment!

138
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,127
This is also trespassing!

139
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:10,091
We have a subpoena for Mr. Hector Baltazar.

140
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:13,427
In connection to the murder of Zach Zamora.

141
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:19,809
Does Inspector Catapang know about this?

142
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:23,479
He is no longer part of the case.

143
00:09:25,147 --> 00:09:28,776
Do you have any other evidence aside
from the statement of Zach's mom?

144
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:37,827
The court wouldn't hand out arrest orders if
we didn't provide strong and solid proof.

145
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:42,206
That's why you should just
hand over Hector Baltazar.

146
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:44,082
So where is Hector anyway?

147
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,626
Mr. Baltazar!

148
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:47,460
Please come out!

149
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:48,838
- Hector Baltazar-you know what, get in there!
- [LEONA] Hold on!

150
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:50,171
- [LEONA] Wait!
- [LIV] Hey don't come in!

151
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:53,259
- Hector please come out already!
- [LIV] This is a violation!

152
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,427
We have a subpoena, get in there!

153
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:57,722
- [LEONA] Wait just a minute!
- [HECTOR] Stop harassing my family.

154
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:01,100
I'm here. I'll come with you.

155
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:10,234
I'll come with you.

156
00:10:10,235 --> 00:10:11,611
[LIV WHISPERS] No!

157
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:24,332
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

158
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:27,752
Dad.

159
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,394
Wait a minute.

160
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:47,020
Let’s wait for Attorney.

161
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:49,523
She’s on her way, before you say anything, okay?

162
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,566
Close your mouth.

163
00:10:50,691 --> 00:10:52,693
You might say something
off to Left Eye.

164
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:53,944
Leona.

165
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:57,948
I already talked to Attorney.

166
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:00,034
She already knows what my decision is.

167
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:03,204
What decision?

168
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,460
I am surrendering.

169
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:12,338
I killed Zach Zamora.

170
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:18,844
It’s true that Zach’s mother and I

171
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:22,056
met at the gym at 3:00 in the afternoon.

172
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,100
I went to his office.

173
00:11:24,934 --> 00:11:31,357
I poured eye drops into his red water flask.

174
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:39,656
Hector, why did you do that?

175
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:42,118
What?
[STUTTERS] Is that true?

176
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:44,829
Dad. You-[STUTTERS]

177
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:47,832
You killed Zach?

178
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:52,378
[LEONA] No.

179
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:56,131
I don’t think your dad did it.

180
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:59,593
Were you coerced by
Left Eye to say that?

181
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:02,095
To say those lies?

182
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,139
Did you force him?

183
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:06,434
Ma’am, I may only have one eye,

184
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:08,560
but I do my job well.

185
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:13,566
Can you please give our family a moment?

186
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:20,698
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

187
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:25,953
Dad.

188
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:27,246
Dad.

189
00:12:27,329 --> 00:12:28,789
How is this is the truth?

190
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:32,126
What happened?

191
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,214
Hector, I know you’re a womanizer, alright?

192
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,387
But you're not a murderer.

193
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:48,976
I have carried it for a long time.

194
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,231
A lot of people got affected.

195
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,818
A lot of people got involved.

196
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:03,407
I thought about escaping.

197
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:10,414
But that will just keep
me away from you both.

198
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:12,792
If I get imprisoned,

199
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:17,504
you will be able to visit me.

200
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:19,882
But why would you kill Zach?

201
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:26,180
Because I was furious.

202
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:30,601
He was blackmailing me and Marga

203
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:33,854
about her affair with Byron.

204
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:40,236
He was going to ruin my
family and my name.

205
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,032
So,

206
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:48,452
I did what I had to do.

207
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:52,581
I killed him.

208
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,877
[HECTOR] Leona.

209
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:00,297
Please take care of Liv.

210
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:03,759
Don’t ever leave her side.

211
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:08,764
Maybe this

212
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:11,559
is my punishment

213
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:16,188
for all of my infidelities.

214
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:21,235
But always remember, Leona,

215
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:28,534
that I really loved you.

216
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:45,342
Liv,

217
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,054
I’m sorry.

218
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:52,683
Even your friends got involved

219
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:54,517
in this mess that I made.

220
00:14:54,518 --> 00:15:00,274
I hope you will be able
to forgive me someday.

221
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,618
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

222
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:15,748
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

223
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:16,665
[LIV MUTTERS]

224
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:18,751
[SNIFFLES]

225
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:22,421
Inspector, maybe we can -

226
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:23,839
Wait a minute. [STUTTERS]

227
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,591
Maybe we can talk it out first.

228
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,218
This is not the truth.

229
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:31,722
Sir.

230
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:33,057
Please wait a minute.

231
00:15:33,058 --> 00:15:36,435
Please, I’m begging you.

232
00:15:36,518 --> 00:15:38,686
Hector, tell them this is not true.

233
00:15:38,687 --> 00:15:41,190
Please tell them now!

234
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:48,238
Please let me take him.

235
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:52,785
[LEONA AND LIV CRYING]

236
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:11,470
I'm sorry, this is all I could afford.

237
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:14,348
Eat up, you haven't eaten since last night.

238
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:28,487
[YANA EXHALES]

239
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:32,908
Uh...

240
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:35,661
Yana, could you please read
our next labor case?

241
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:37,121
The Chua versus Clave?

242
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:39,581
What did the Supreme Court say about that?

243
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,960
Uh...

244
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,712
It says here,

245
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:48,131
It says here that if the two eventually
fell in love despite the disparity

246
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:52,886
of their ages and academic levels
then this lends truism...

247
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:58,017
to the fact that...

248
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:02,146
the heart has reasons in
which reason does not know.

249
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,858
Oh, Justice is so sweet there.

250
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:06,859
What about you guys?

251
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:10,070
Would you fall in love with
someone not on your level?

252
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:12,155
[YANA'S CLASSMATE] Hmm...

253
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:13,032
Yeah, of course!

254
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:15,743
Do you think it's possible?

255
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:17,536
[YANA'S CLASSMATE] Nothing's impossible!

256
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,246
That's true, what about you Yana?

257
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,125
I'm sorry guys, um...

258
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,210
I'll be back, okay?

259
00:17:25,544 --> 00:17:27,796
I just need to go somewhere, I'm so sorry!

260
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:31,049
Oh, Gabo,

261
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,719
it's a good thing you
dropped by before you left.

262
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,721
Take care abroad, alright?

263
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,472
